I hope I'm intruding.

101
00:12:03,272 --> 00:12:05,502
Why, Professor, when did you get in?

102
00:12:05,674 --> 00:12:07,642
Just now. I had to make up an exam.

103
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:09,710
- I've got the whole holiday before me.
- Good.

104
00:12:09,879 --> 00:12:11,904
- Need any help celebrating?
- Nadine.

105
00:12:12,081 --> 00:12:14,413
- Johnny.
- I brought you something.

106
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:18,781
Oh, Johnny! Oh, Johnny, what a darling.

107
00:12:18,954 --> 00:12:20,945
I know just the dress
to wear him with.

108
00:12:21,123 --> 00:12:22,988
Essie. Essie!

109
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:26,458
- Take your coat off.
- Look what Mr. Harrow brought us.

110
00:12:26,629 --> 00:12:28,756
- Another one?
- For my new beige suit.

111
00:12:28,931 --> 00:12:30,626
Who pushed you in the face?

112
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,428
I want to give you a farewell tonight.
Where will it be? Delmonico's?

113
00:12:33,602 --> 00:12:35,035
- Please sit down.
- Sherry's?

114
00:12:35,204 --> 00:12:36,933
You decide, you're the party boy.

115
00:12:37,106 --> 00:12:39,097
Gosh, I wish you two weren't leaving.

116
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:41,104
I'm not leaving.

117
00:12:41,410 --> 00:12:43,037
Oh, but, darling.

118
00:12:43,212 --> 00:12:44,770
I signed that contract, Don.

119
00:12:45,548 --> 00:12:48,312
- You what?
- I signed it this afternoon.

120
00:12:48,551 --> 00:12:50,610
I'm going into a show, Johnny.

121
00:12:50,886 --> 00:12:52,547
Why, you're kidding.

122
00:12:52,721 --> 00:12:55,212
We've signed contracts
for the next six months.

123
00:12:55,391 --> 00:12:57,518
You did. I didn't.

124
00:12:57,693 --> 00:12:59,820
There's no way they can hold me.

125
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:04,024
I know it must sound
terribly selfish of me, Don...

126
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,168
...but I've got to think of myself.

127
00:13:06,335 --> 00:13:09,930
After all, there's no future in my just being
a ballroom dancer.

128
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:12,640
You do understand, don't you?

129
00:13:13,075 --> 00:13:15,339
No. I'm sorry.

130
00:13:15,511 --> 00:13:17,240
I don't understand.

131
00:13:21,650 --> 00:13:23,618
- Don...
- Johnny, you understand.

132
00:13:23,786 --> 00:13:25,014
Frankly, no.

133
00:13:25,187 --> 00:13:27,678
You can't be serious.
It doesn't make sense.

134
00:13:27,857 --> 00:13:31,452
- I always thought you and Don were...
- Did you?

135
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:35,720
He's done everything in the world for you.
Why walk out on him now?

136
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:37,126
Johnny...

137
00:13:37,299 --> 00:13:39,494
...don't you know?

138
00:13:41,337 --> 00:13:44,397
I think I'd better go and look for Don.

139
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:46,632
We have a dinner date.

140
00:13:47,943 --> 00:13:50,878
- We'll be back.
- But...

141
00:13:55,017 --> 00:13:57,713
- Can you drown a brunette in this?
- How tall is she?

142
00:13:57,887 --> 00:13:59,718
Five-foot-six.

143
00:14:04,159 --> 00:14:07,458
- Try that.
- Two bourbons, Mike.

144
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:12,959
She's not going to Chicago.

145
00:14:13,135 --> 00:14:16,502
He travels fastest who travels alone,
I always say.

146
00:14:16,672 --> 00:14:18,936
Right. I bet you know
a lot about women.

147
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:21,167
I should. I've been single all my life.

148
00:14:21,343 --> 00:14:23,470
- You're a smart fella...
- Mike.

149
00:14:23,646 --> 00:14:26,706
Work behind a bar,
you get to know what makes people tick.

150
00:14:26,882 --> 00:14:30,340
This place is like a clinic.
People come in with their troubles.

151
00:14:30,519 --> 00:14:32,214
Well, if you listen, you learn.

152
00:14:32,388 --> 00:14:36,222
Been here 15 years, and I can boil down
trouble into two classifications.

153
00:14:36,392 --> 00:14:39,520
- Yeah? What are they?
- Women and their mothers.

154
00:14:39,895 --> 00:14:42,193
- Hello, Don.
- Hi.

155
00:14:42,364 --> 00:14:43,626
Oh, hello, Professor.

156
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:46,393
- What'll it be? Blond or brunette?
- The same.

157
00:14:46,569 --> 00:14:48,935
Brunettes. They're the ones
you got to watch.

158
00:14:49,104 --> 00:14:50,571
How did you find me?

159
00:14:50,739 --> 00:14:54,197
I didn't have my crystal ball,
so I just followed you here.

160
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:57,608
Meet my friend Mike.
He's a disciple of Aristophanes.

161
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:59,907
- How do you do?
- Pleased to know you.

162
00:15:00,082 --> 00:15:01,982
Don, I'm taking you back to Nadine.

163
00:15:03,018 --> 00:15:04,485
Did she send you for me?

164
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:07,053
- No, but...
- That's the trouble with college.

165
00:15:07,222 --> 00:15:10,749
You've been reading.
There's more sense in this than in a library.

166
00:15:10,926 --> 00:15:13,622
- Right, Mike?
- Education's all right.

167
00:15:13,796 --> 00:15:15,388
It's the people who spoil it.

168
00:15:15,564 --> 00:15:17,429
Nadine didn't mean what she said.

169
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:18,862
You two belong together.

170
00:15:19,034 --> 00:15:23,027
If she'd just fallen in love with some guy,
I could do something about it.

171
00:15:23,205 --> 00:15:27,141
You know she can't get along without you,
or you without her.

172
00:15:27,309 --> 00:15:29,641
Who says I can't get along without her?

173
00:15:29,812 --> 00:15:33,077
See those girls. Any one of them
has as much talent as she.

174
00:15:33,248 --> 00:15:35,546
You're crazy. There's no one like Nadine.

175
00:15:35,718 --> 00:15:39,017
- Dances like an angel, knows how to dress...
- I taught her.

176
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:41,622
- I could take any of those girls...
- Show's on.

177
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:44,156
I could take any one of them
and do the same.

178
00:15:44,326 --> 00:15:46,351
She still wouldn't be like Nadine.

179
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:48,792
I promised I'd get right back. You coming?

180
00:15:48,964 --> 00:15:50,192
She knows where I am.

181
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:53,130
She'll come around when contracts
are out of season.

182
00:15:53,335 --> 00:15:54,563
You sure?

183
00:15:54,737 --> 00:15:56,364
No, thanks. You run along.

184
00:15:56,772 --> 00:15:58,865
All right. Take care of him, Mike.

185
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,872
Okay.

186
00:16:02,845 --> 00:16:04,437
Any one of them.

187
00:16:04,613 --> 00:16:06,171
Do I need her?

188
00:16:06,348 --> 00:16:09,977
Well, no man is an island.

189
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:14,246
- Thanks, Mike.
- Every man is a piece of the continent...

190
00:16:14,556 --> 00:16:17,047
...a part of the main.

191
00:16:29,605 --> 00:16:31,163
Sorry.

192
00:16:32,207 --> 00:16:34,232
Yeah, I think you'll do.

193
00:16:34,443 --> 00:16:37,276
- I'll do what?
- I'm looking for someone to dance with.

194
00:16:37,446 --> 00:16:39,676
- Wrong number.
- I need a new dancing partner.

195
00:16:39,848 --> 00:16:41,315
I'll give you $ 100 a week.

196
00:16:41,483 --> 00:16:43,713
A hundred doll... That would never do.

197
00:16:43,886 --> 00:16:45,911
- All right, $ 150.
- A hundred and fifty.

198
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,453
Thank you. Now may I go?

199
00:16:47,623 --> 00:16:49,648
Sure. Just a minute. Here's my card.

200
00:16:49,825 --> 00:16:53,090
I'll get a rehearsal hall at Michael's.
Know where it is?

201
00:16:53,262 --> 00:16:54,490
Yeah.

202
00:16:54,663 --> 00:16:57,962
All right, tomorrow morning, 10:00.

203
00:16:59,368 --> 00:17:01,097
You'll wait for me.

204
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:04,504
- Hi, Hannah.
- Hi. Will you help me into this?

205
00:17:04,673 --> 00:17:06,903
- Sure.
- Thank you.

206
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:12,380
There's a nice guy.
He's unhappy and a little lonely...

207
00:17:12,548 --> 00:17:15,016
I'll bet he's lonely.
Got away from his keeper.

208
00:17:15,184 --> 00:17:19,951
You know what he wanted me to do?
Give up a good, steady, $ 15-a-week job.

209
00:17:20,122 --> 00:17:22,056
- Thanks.
- I didn't catch his name.

210
00:17:22,491 --> 00:17:24,220
Don Hewes.

211
00:17:25,494 --> 00:17:27,189
Don Hewes?!

212
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:41,500
<i>I was born in Michigan</i>

213
00:17:41,777 --> 00:17:44,439
<i>And I wish and wish again</i>

214
00:17:44,646 --> 00:17:46,477
<i>That I was back</i>

215
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:51,847
<i>In the town where I was born</i>

216
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:55,586
<i>There's a farm in Michigan</i>

217
00:17:55,858 --> 00:17:58,725
<i>And I'd like to fish again</i>

218
00:17:58,894 --> 00:18:01,761
<i>In the river that flows</i>

219
00:18:01,930 --> 00:18:06,230
<i>Beside the field of waving corn</i>

220
00:18:06,468 --> 00:18:11,269
<i>A lonesome soul am I</i>

221
00:18:11,573 --> 00:18:15,703
<i>Here's the reason why</i>

222
00:18:15,878 --> 00:18:19,541
<i>I want to go back</i>
<i>I want to go back</i>

223
00:18:19,715 --> 00:18:23,947
<i>I want to go back to the farm</i>

224
00:18:24,186 --> 00:18:26,746
<i>Far away from harm</i>

225
00:18:26,922 --> 00:18:30,323
<i>With a milk pail on my arm</i>

226
00:18:30,492 --> 00:18:34,053
<i>I miss the rooster</i>
<i>The one that used to</i>

227
00:18:34,263 --> 00:18:38,461
<i>Wake me up at 4 a.m.</i>

228
00:18:38,667 --> 00:18:43,832
<i>I think your great big city's</i>
<i>Very pretty</i>

229
00:18:44,139 --> 00:18:48,303
<i>Nevertheless, I want to be there</i>
<i>I want to see there</i>

230
00:18:48,477 --> 00:18:52,436
<i>A certain someone full of charm</i>

231
00:18:52,714 --> 00:18:56,514
<i>That's why I wish again</i>
<i>That I was in Michigan</i>

232
00:18:56,752 --> 00:19:00,051
<i>Down on the farm</i>

233
00:19:02,891 --> 00:19:06,224
<i>I wanna go back</i>
<i>I wanna go back</i>

234
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:11,230
<i>I wanna go back</i>
<i>To that old farm</i>

235
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:14,627
<i>Far away from harm</i>

236
00:19:14,803 --> 00:19:19,137
<i>With a milk pail on my arm</i>

237
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:21,671
<i>I miss the rooster</i>

238
00:19:21,844 --> 00:19:27,646
<i>The rooster that used to</i>
<i>Wake me up at 4 a.m.</i>

239
00:19:28,016 --> 00:19:33,784
<i>I think your great big city's</i>
<i>Very pretty</i>

240
00:19:34,056 --> 00:19:38,891
<i>Nevertheless, I want to be there</i>
<i>I want to see there</i>

241
00:19:39,061 --> 00:19:43,395
<i>A certain someone full of charm</i>

242
00:19:43,699 --> 00:19:47,100
<i>That's why I wish again</i>

243
00:19:47,502 --> 00:19:52,735
<i>That I was in Michigan</i>

244
00:19:53,242 --> 00:19:56,609
<i>Down on</i>

245
00:19:56,778 --> 00:20:00,236
<i>The farm</i>

246
00:20:06,555 --> 00:20:08,455
She's not coming.
Come on, let's go.

247
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:11,115
You said 10:00.
She's only a minute late.

248
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:13,853
She won't be here.
At least I hope she won't.

249
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:17,159
To tell the truth,
I got emotional last night.

250
00:20:17,332 --> 00:20:21,860
I can't remember what happened,
but I seem to have been carried away.

251
00:20:22,037 --> 00:20:24,232
Well, there goes five bucks.

252
00:20:24,406 --> 00:20:28,638
Here. It's worth ten to get out of it
this easily. I'll see you later.

253
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:31,301
Am I late? I'm sorry, Mr. Hewes.

254
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:35,814
I couldn't catch a bus.
It is Easter Sunday, you know.

255
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:38,578
I walked.

256
00:20:38,754 --> 00:20:42,713
You should have seen Mr. Pastini's face
when I quit my job last night.

257
00:20:42,891 --> 00:20:44,984
He was furious.

258
00:20:46,895 --> 00:20:48,453
Good morning.

259
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:50,461
Say that again.

260
00:20:50,966 --> 00:20:54,766
- Good morning.
- I mean about quitting your job.

261
00:20:55,737 --> 00:20:58,035
You... You told me to quit my job.
You said...

262
00:20:58,206 --> 00:21:00,640
I know what I said. This is Marty.

263
00:21:01,209 --> 00:21:02,836
- How do you...?
- Your name is?

264
00:21:03,011 --> 00:21:05,036
Hannah Brown.

265
00:21:05,213 --> 00:21:07,204
Oh, we can fix that. Sure, we can.

266
00:21:07,382 --> 00:21:09,111
Now, there's nothing to this.

267
00:21:09,284 --> 00:21:11,775
I lead for four counts,
starting with your left.

268
00:21:11,954 --> 00:21:14,787
Half-turn to the right,
drop to a curtsy as I bow.

269
00:21:14,957 --> 00:21:18,484
On five, rise slowly. Twist to the right,
then to the left.

270
00:21:18,660 --> 00:21:22,096
Right arm fully extended
in preparation for the first lift.

271
00:21:23,432 --> 00:21:25,263
I beg your pardon?

272
00:21:26,168 --> 00:21:28,068
You understand, don't you?

273
00:21:28,303 --> 00:21:29,634
No.

274
00:21:30,605 --> 00:21:35,269
Miss Brown, what idiot ever
told you you were a dancer?

275
00:21:35,711 --> 00:21:37,406
You did.

276
00:21:37,579 --> 00:21:39,672
If I did, you're a dancer.

277
00:21:39,848 --> 00:21:42,715
Now, let's start this thing
right from the beginning.

278
00:21:43,118 --> 00:21:45,848
Now, left foot forward, please.

279
00:21:47,456 --> 00:21:49,447
Left foot forward.

280
00:21:51,226 --> 00:21:52,557
You're gonna hate me.

281
00:21:52,728 --> 00:21:53,956
- I am?
- Yes.

282
00:21:54,129 --> 00:21:56,927
You know your left foot
from your right, don't you?

283
00:21:57,099 --> 00:21:58,964
- I'm never sure.
- Oh, no.

284
00:21:59,134 --> 00:22:02,194
This isn't my fault.
When I was little, I was left-handed.

285
00:22:02,371 --> 00:22:06,330
But the doctor told my mother
I might grow up to be a dangerous criminal.

286
00:22:06,508 --> 00:22:11,275
So they made me do things with my
right hand, and now I'm not sure anymore.

287
00:22:13,348 --> 00:22:14,940
How did you dance in the show?

288
00:22:15,117 --> 00:22:18,314
When I danced in the show,
I had a garter on my left leg...

289
00:22:18,487 --> 00:22:21,888
...but I haven't got a garter today.

290
00:22:30,198 --> 00:22:32,132
That is your left leg.

291
00:22:32,300 --> 00:22:34,427
That is your right leg. See?

292
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:36,127
Yes.

293
00:22:36,304 --> 00:22:37,828
Here.

294
00:22:38,006 --> 00:22:40,531
- Here's a rubber band. Put that on.
- Thank you.

295
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:51,544
Did I say I got carried away?

296
00:22:54,089 --> 00:22:57,115
- Ready.
- All right. Over here.

297
00:22:57,325 --> 00:22:58,758
Let's have some music.

298
00:22:58,927 --> 00:23:01,589
This is what you do. And...

299
00:23:01,763 --> 00:23:06,097
...left, right, left, right.

300
00:23:06,268 --> 00:23:12,696
Turn right. Curtsy.
And twist right.

301
00:23:12,874 --> 00:23:16,571
Twist left. Arm out.

302
00:23:16,745 --> 00:23:20,875
Lift, two, three, four.

303
00:23:21,049 --> 00:23:25,679
One, two, right, left, right.

304
00:23:25,854 --> 00:23:30,518
Good. One, two, three, four.

305
00:23:30,692 --> 00:23:34,856
Turn, two, three, four.

306
00:23:35,030 --> 00:23:38,966
Turn, two, three. Change.

307
00:23:39,134 --> 00:23:41,932
That's it. Now softer.

308
00:23:42,104 --> 00:23:43,537
Very quiet.

309
00:23:43,705 --> 00:23:46,105
Don't take your eyes from mine.

310
00:23:46,575 --> 00:23:48,736
You just look as if you're in pain.

311
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:50,878
I am. The rubber band's too tight.

312
00:23:51,046 --> 00:23:53,981
- Well, then take it off.
- It won't take me a minute.

313
00:23:54,149 --> 00:23:58,950
- I didn't know. It stopped the circulation.
- Pick it up about here. Right there.

314
00:23:59,754 --> 00:24:05,750
- I know it's gonna be better now.
- And, one, two, three, four.

315
00:24:05,927 --> 00:24:08,919
Now, look at me intimately, caressingly.

316
00:24:09,097 --> 00:24:13,431
Make every man in the audience
wish that he were in my shoes.

317
00:24:13,602 --> 00:24:15,593
That's the idea.

318
00:24:15,770 --> 00:24:18,170
Closer. Closer.

319
00:24:18,340 --> 00:24:21,173
More. More.

320
00:24:21,343 --> 00:24:26,906
Lunch. Marty, about an hour
I think will do, don't you?

321
00:24:27,082 --> 00:24:29,778
- Leave the music?
- I've got the place all afternoon.

322
00:24:29,951 --> 00:24:32,852
- It won't make any difference.
- Okay.

323
00:24:38,493 --> 00:24:40,120
Was I too terrible?

324
00:24:40,295 --> 00:24:42,160
No, no.

325
00:24:42,531 --> 00:24:45,227
You know, I've never really danced before.

326
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,766
You're going to be fine.

327
00:24:48,036 --> 00:24:51,631
Mr. Hewes, you know,
you don't have to go on with this.

328
00:24:51,806 --> 00:24:53,034
- Now, look...
- I mean it.

329
00:24:53,208 --> 00:24:56,336
You're a wonderful dancer.
You could get anybody to dance.

330
00:24:56,511 --> 00:24:57,876
You could get the best.

331
00:24:58,046 --> 00:24:59,843
I don't want the best. I want you.

332
00:25:00,015 --> 00:25:04,042
I mean, look. You didn't ask me for the job.
I picked you.

333
00:25:04,219 --> 00:25:07,416
You're gonna make good.
Not just for your sake, but for mine.

334
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:09,580
It means a great deal to me.

335
00:25:11,226 --> 00:25:14,389
- It does?
- Come on.

336
00:25:22,404 --> 00:25:26,636
Oh, look. The Easter Parade.
Isn't it beautiful?

337
00:25:26,808 --> 00:25:29,572
It's all right, if you like Easter Parades.

338
00:25:34,049 --> 00:25:36,449
I can't believe I'm really here.

339
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:39,644
I used to read about the Easter Parade
in New York...

340
00:25:39,821 --> 00:25:41,755
- Excuse me.
- In New York.

341
00:25:41,923 --> 00:25:46,326
And then I'd look at the pictures
of the women in their lovely clothes...

342
00:25:46,494 --> 00:25:50,726
...dream that maybe someday l...
Here I am.

343
00:25:50,899 --> 00:25:52,491
Oh, look.

344
00:25:57,105 --> 00:25:59,369
May I take your picture, Miss Hale?

345
00:26:00,475 --> 00:26:02,306
Hold it, Miss Hale.

346
00:26:02,477 --> 00:26:04,206
Just one more, Miss Hale.

347
00:26:04,379 --> 00:26:06,779
- Good. Thank you.
- Miss Hale.

348
00:26:07,349 --> 00:26:09,442
Thank you.

349
00:26:20,629 --> 00:26:22,893
Isn't she wonderful-looking!

350
00:26:23,064 --> 00:26:24,725
Even with that silly hat.

351
00:26:24,899 --> 00:26:27,834
- What's the matter with it?
- She must be very important.

352
00:26:28,003 --> 00:26:30,062
Look at her clothes, the way she walks.

353
00:26:30,238 --> 00:26:31,762
See her nose?

354
00:26:31,940 --> 00:26:34,374
One year from now,
you're gonna put it out of joint.

355
00:26:34,542 --> 00:26:36,942
- I am?
- Next Easter, when we walk down here...

356
00:26:37,112 --> 00:26:40,047
...you'll cause more excitement
than an earthquake.

357
00:26:40,215 --> 00:26:43,810
Every photographer will break his neck
to take your picture.

358
00:26:43,985 --> 00:26:47,648
One year from today, no one
is gonna notice her when they look at you.

359
00:26:54,396 --> 00:26:55,954
- This is lovely.
- That one.

360
00:26:56,131 --> 00:26:58,065
Yes, Mr. Hewes.

361
00:27:03,138 --> 00:27:05,504
May I see that, please?

362
00:27:06,408 --> 00:27:10,208
- Isn't this beautiful?
- Wrap this up. Just send all the things.

363
00:27:10,378 --> 00:27:12,437
Yes, Mr. Hewes.

364
00:27:12,614 --> 00:27:15,344
- You ready?
- Yes, Mr. Hewes.

365
00:27:24,159 --> 00:27:27,026
Mr. Hewes, I...

366
00:27:27,195 --> 00:27:29,356
These dresses are beautiful, but...

367
00:27:29,531 --> 00:27:33,865
- But what?
- Do they look like me, like Hannah Brown?

368
00:27:34,035 --> 00:27:37,971
There is no more Hannah Brown.
From now on, you're Juanita.

369
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:41,034
If you wanted a Juanita,
why did you pick me?

370
00:27:41,209 --> 00:27:43,973
Now, don't get mad. This is business.

371
00:27:44,145 --> 00:27:45,806
A girl dancer has to be exotic.

372
00:27:45,980 --> 00:27:47,470
She has to be...

373
00:27:47,649 --> 00:27:49,014
...a peach.

374
00:27:49,517 --> 00:27:51,280
I suppose I'm a lemon.

375
00:27:51,453 --> 00:27:52,818
No. Here's what I mean.

376
00:27:52,987 --> 00:27:56,718
Now, when you walk down the street alone
do men try to catch your eye?

377
00:27:56,958 --> 00:27:58,323
Of course they do.

378
00:27:58,493 --> 00:28:01,257
Do they turn around and look at you?

379
00:28:02,731 --> 00:28:04,460
L... I don't know.

380
00:28:04,632 --> 00:28:06,793
I never turn around to look at them.

381
00:28:06,968 --> 00:28:10,165
Here, give me those.
You go ahead. I wanna try something.

382
00:28:10,338 --> 00:28:13,102
Just walk on ahead. I wanna see.

383
00:28:39,934 --> 00:28:41,925
Right! You've got it.

384
00:28:42,103 --> 00:28:43,900
Thank you.

385
00:29:04,092 --> 00:29:06,390
Let go of my hand.
Let go of my hand.

386
00:29:19,641 --> 00:29:21,165
Left.

387
00:30:30,612 --> 00:30:32,045
- I'm afraid...
- Don't worry.

388
00:30:32,213 --> 00:30:34,408
- It was just the first performance.
- I was so nervous.

389
00:30:34,582 --> 00:30:37,415
One thing you mustn't do:
Get a stranglehold on me.

390
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:39,143
It pulls me off balance.

391
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:41,379
- I know.
- Relax, you'll be all right.

392
00:30:41,556 --> 00:30:44,787
I hope so. Did you send these?

393
00:30:44,959 --> 00:30:46,950
- Yes.
- They're very beautiful.

394
00:30:47,128 --> 00:30:50,325
- You go change, we'll have dinner.
- May I bring my roses?

395
00:30:50,498 --> 00:30:52,022
Sure.

396
00:30:52,734 --> 00:30:55,931
- Keep sending flowers. It's good business.
- Yes, sir.

397
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:57,731
How did the act go, Mr. Hewes?

398
00:30:57,906 --> 00:30:59,498
One bow.

399
00:30:59,674 --> 00:31:01,733
Too bad.

400
00:31:03,811 --> 00:31:05,073
Eddie. Eddie.

401
00:31:05,246 --> 00:31:07,976
Eddie, get down there. Sit. Sit.

402
00:31:08,149 --> 00:31:11,243
All right, everybody sit down. Sit down.

403
00:31:11,419 --> 00:31:13,853
Tomorrow we'd better get some dogs
in the act.

404
00:31:19,994 --> 00:31:21,621
- Here's the young lady.
- Nadine.

405
00:31:21,896 --> 00:31:24,558
Darling, I was so excited
when I got your message.

406
00:31:24,732 --> 00:31:27,496
- When did you get in town?
- I got in this morning.

407
00:31:27,669 --> 00:31:31,435
I can recommend fillet of sole meuniere.

408
00:31:31,606 --> 00:31:34,370
- Monsieur had that last night.
- Last night?

409
00:31:34,542 --> 00:31:37,102
- We'll order later.
- Very well. I'll remove this.

410
00:31:37,278 --> 00:31:38,939
We're expecting someone else.

411
00:31:39,113 --> 00:31:41,741
- Luncheon for three?
- Who's joining us?

412
00:31:41,916 --> 00:31:44,407
Someone who's very important
to both of us.

413
00:31:44,586 --> 00:31:48,113
Johnny, I'm going to meet your father.

414
00:31:48,289 --> 00:31:52,055
Look, Nadine, our future is so far away.

415
00:31:52,226 --> 00:31:54,319
I have years of school ahead of me...

416
00:31:54,495 --> 00:31:57,191
I thought you were almost finished
with law school.

417
00:31:57,365 --> 00:32:02,735
I am, I am. But I've decided
to become a doctor.

418
00:32:03,237 --> 00:32:04,829
I'll wait.

419
00:32:08,776 --> 00:32:12,769
Well, it's liable to be a tough struggle.

420
00:32:12,947 --> 00:32:16,212
I won't inherit any of my father's money
until I'm at least...

421
00:32:16,384 --> 00:32:20,548
...fifty-five.
- Fifty-five? That's an odd arrangement.

422
00:32:21,022 --> 00:32:26,517
Well, Father was very eccentric.
He hated children.

423
00:32:26,694 --> 00:32:28,821
Oh, I love children.

424
00:32:29,097 --> 00:32:31,327
Maybe you could adopt one.

425
00:32:31,499 --> 00:32:33,023
- There he is.
- Hello, Johnny.

426
00:32:33,201 --> 00:32:36,534
Donald. If you'll forgive me,
I have an oral psychology exam.

427
00:32:36,704 --> 00:32:40,504
You what? You'll flunk it.

428
00:32:42,443 --> 00:32:43,671
Hello, Nadine.

429
00:32:43,845 --> 00:32:46,712
I'm glad you're here, Don.
Sit down, won't you?

430
00:32:46,881 --> 00:32:49,509
- Thanks.
- I've been wanting to talk to you.

431
00:32:49,684 --> 00:32:51,049
You have?

432
00:32:51,219 --> 00:32:53,278
You look tired.

433
00:32:53,454 --> 00:32:56,582
Breaking in new routines.
You remember it.

434
00:32:56,758 --> 00:32:58,248
It seems years ago.

435
00:32:58,426 --> 00:33:01,054
I can tell you how many minutes it's been.

436
00:33:01,496 --> 00:33:03,555
Is the gentleman coming back?

437
00:33:03,731 --> 00:33:06,222
Yes, but not for lunch.

438
00:33:06,401 --> 00:33:08,767
Luncheon for two?

439
00:33:08,936 --> 00:33:12,167
We have some very fine
broiled lamb chops today.

440
00:33:12,340 --> 00:33:14,205
We'll order later. Thank you.

441
00:33:14,375 --> 00:33:15,603
Very good, monsieur.

442
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:19,873
It's...

443
00:33:20,048 --> 00:33:21,572
...very nice to see you.

444
00:33:21,749 --> 00:33:23,808
I've been hearing about your new act.

445
00:33:23,985 --> 00:33:26,078
It's not really broken in yet.

446
00:33:26,254 --> 00:33:29,746
It seems so strange dancing
with somebody else.

447
00:33:29,924 --> 00:33:33,860
Remember our opening night in Boston?
Three encores, eight bows.

448
00:33:34,028 --> 00:33:35,689
We stopped the show cold.

449
00:33:35,863 --> 00:33:37,626
I still have those reviews.

450
00:33:37,799 --> 00:33:41,667
- Listen, baby, I was thinking...
- I start rehearsal soon for my new show.

451
00:33:41,836 --> 00:33:44,066
Are you going through
with that crazy idea?

452
00:33:44,238 --> 00:33:48,265
Crazy? Because I don't wanna spend
the rest of my life being a common hoofer?

453
00:33:48,443 --> 00:33:51,537
It was good enough
when I took you out of that chorus.

454
00:33:51,879 --> 00:33:55,007
You think if it hadn't been
for you, I'd still be there?

455
00:33:55,516 --> 00:33:58,952
That's possible. The fellow who ran
that place wasn't Ziegfeld.

456
00:33:59,620 --> 00:34:02,919
Let me tell you something.
If you can get along without me...

457
00:34:03,091 --> 00:34:06,527
...tell that seamstress dancing with you
to stop imitating me.

458
00:34:06,694 --> 00:34:08,924
Imitating you? She's never even seen you.

459
00:34:09,097 --> 00:34:10,655
No, but you have.

460
00:34:10,832 --> 00:34:13,323
All my friends are laughing.

461
00:34:17,972 --> 00:34:19,564
- That's it.
- You bet that's it.

462
00:34:19,741 --> 00:34:22,767
- And you tell that Miss...
- Brown. Hannah Brown.

463
00:34:22,944 --> 00:34:25,913
- I have something to do.
- Don't you dare leave me alone.

464
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:28,548
You forget, honey.
You're on your own now.

465
00:34:31,052 --> 00:34:34,078
The gentleman is coming back?

466
00:34:34,255 --> 00:34:36,280
You're wrong twice.

467
00:34:36,457 --> 00:34:39,290
Luncheon for one?

468
00:34:40,394 --> 00:34:43,158
May I suggest the sirloin tips
to mademoiselle?

469
00:34:43,331 --> 00:34:45,561
Thank you. I'm not hungry.

470
00:34:45,733 --> 00:34:47,166
Certainly, mademoiselle.

471
00:34:47,335 --> 00:34:49,565
Come in again soon.

472
00:34:50,338 --> 00:34:52,363
Bring your friends.

473
00:34:54,175 --> 00:34:55,904
How much is that, please?

474
00:34:56,077 --> 00:34:58,978
Let's see. Roast beef, pie, milk.

475
00:34:59,147 --> 00:35:01,342
That'll be 15 cents.

476
00:35:03,985 --> 00:35:05,885
- Thank you.
- Thank you. Bye.

477
00:35:06,053 --> 00:35:07,645
Goodbye.

478
