- You don't want to order.

699
00:50:54,266 --> 00:50:55,927
Yes, we do.

700
00:50:56,101 --> 00:50:58,695
The specialty tonight is beef stroganoff.

701
00:50:58,871 --> 00:51:01,362
- But you wouldn't like it.
- It sounds wonderful.

702
00:51:01,540 --> 00:51:03,405
- Make it two.
- Two beef stroganoffs.

703
00:51:03,575 --> 00:51:07,272
- Yes. What about a salad?
- Salad? There is only one salad.

704
00:51:07,446 --> 00:51:09,004
Salad Franois.

705
00:51:09,181 --> 00:51:11,581
- Your salad?
- Let's try it.

706
00:51:11,750 --> 00:51:14,548
- Try it?
- What's in it?

707
00:51:16,955 --> 00:51:18,752
I'll show you.

708
00:51:22,060 --> 00:51:24,585
This salad has been handed down...

709
00:51:24,763 --> 00:51:28,529
...from my great-grandfather
to my grandfather...

710
00:51:28,700 --> 00:51:32,932
...to my father, and from my father to me.

711
00:51:33,105 --> 00:51:34,333
Spice...

712
00:51:34,506 --> 00:51:36,371
...from India.

713
00:51:37,743 --> 00:51:40,678
Herb from Africa.

714
00:51:42,381 --> 00:51:43,746
Garlic...

715
00:51:43,916 --> 00:51:45,508
...perfume for a gourmet.

716
00:51:45,684 --> 00:51:48,778
I gently rub the inside of the bowl.

717
00:51:50,489 --> 00:51:52,753
Petits pois from France.

718
00:52:00,766 --> 00:52:03,599
Apartment 24B.

719
00:52:06,738 --> 00:52:08,069
Egg...

720
00:52:08,240 --> 00:52:10,037
...from a chicken.

721
00:52:12,044 --> 00:52:13,705
Lemon.

722
00:52:14,079 --> 00:52:16,980
You must be ruthless.

723
00:52:19,351 --> 00:52:21,979
Cheese, Parmesan from Italy.

724
00:52:33,432 --> 00:52:34,922
I put them in anyway.

725
00:52:40,005 --> 00:52:43,998
Onion from Bermuda.
You slice the onion very thin.

726
00:52:44,843 --> 00:52:47,243
This gives the salad flavor.

727
00:52:47,412 --> 00:52:50,347
It makes it bright, refreshing...

728
00:52:50,515 --> 00:52:52,346
...and gay.

729
00:52:57,122 --> 00:53:00,489
Mix, mix, toss, toss.
Mix, mix, toss, toss.

730
00:53:00,659 --> 00:53:03,651
Toss, toss, mix, mix.
Toss, toss, mix, mix.

731
00:53:03,829 --> 00:53:07,265
Mix, toss, toss, mix.
Mix, mix, toss, toss.

732
00:53:16,041 --> 00:53:17,508
I don't think so.

733
00:53:24,583 --> 00:53:26,073
It's very nice here.

734
00:53:27,119 --> 00:53:29,144
I like it.

735
00:53:32,724 --> 00:53:35,056
Now, what did you wanna
talk to me about?

736
00:53:37,863 --> 00:53:40,331
You and Don are very good friends,
aren't you?

737
00:53:40,499 --> 00:53:41,727
Yes.

738
00:53:41,900 --> 00:53:43,765
- Was he ever married?
- No.

739
00:53:43,936 --> 00:53:45,665
Engaged?

740
00:53:45,837 --> 00:53:48,397
I only ask because I'm curious.

741
00:53:48,573 --> 00:53:50,598
He never talks about himself.

742
00:53:50,776 --> 00:53:52,710
Just about dancing.

743
00:53:53,178 --> 00:53:56,807
- Everything is strictly business.
- That's a good idea.

744
00:53:58,083 --> 00:53:59,573
Sometimes...

745
00:53:59,751 --> 00:54:03,016
...if we make a mistake in the show,
he'll ask if I'll stay...

746
00:54:03,188 --> 00:54:04,815
...and rehearse with him.

747
00:54:04,990 --> 00:54:07,959
We go out and have a late supper...

748
00:54:08,126 --> 00:54:09,718
...and we dance...

749
00:54:09,895 --> 00:54:12,295
...just the two of us.

750
00:54:13,732 --> 00:54:16,326
Sometimes I make mistakes on purpose.

751
00:54:17,202 --> 00:54:20,865
You know, I think that Franois was right,
there are three of us here.

752
00:54:21,606 --> 00:54:23,005
Look...

753
00:54:23,175 --> 00:54:26,736
...supposing Don were interested
in someone else?

754
00:54:28,914 --> 00:54:30,541
Do you mean Nadine?

755
00:54:30,716 --> 00:54:33,207
Well, they used to work together.

756
00:54:35,854 --> 00:54:39,950
- He was in love with her, wasn't he?
- I don't know. I guess so.

757
00:54:40,125 --> 00:54:42,184
Well, he isn't anymore.

758
00:54:42,361 --> 00:54:44,261
He turned down the Ziegfeld show.

759
00:54:44,429 --> 00:54:45,657
Why?

760
00:54:45,831 --> 00:54:49,631
Because he said that she didn't belong
in the same show with me.

761
00:54:49,801 --> 00:54:51,564
I agree with him.

762
00:54:51,737 --> 00:54:55,070
Now, is there anything more
that I can tell you about Don?

763
00:54:55,907 --> 00:54:57,306
No.

764
00:54:57,676 --> 00:54:59,871
Good. Now let's talk about us.

765
00:55:00,045 --> 00:55:05,142
Did you know that scientists say that people
fall in love quickest during a rainstorm?

766
00:55:06,852 --> 00:55:08,877
I can prove that.

767
00:55:10,555 --> 00:55:13,456
Because that's when I fell
in love with you.

768
00:55:16,595 --> 00:55:18,119
You're not angry?

769
00:55:18,296 --> 00:55:21,060
Angry? No, I'm not angry.

770
00:55:21,233 --> 00:55:23,531
I'm very proud.

771
00:55:24,836 --> 00:55:26,827
Do you think that...

772
00:55:27,239 --> 00:55:29,298
...you could love me?

773
00:55:30,876 --> 00:55:34,312
Oh, Johnny, I'd be such a fool if I didn't.

774
00:55:34,479 --> 00:55:36,276
But...

775
00:55:36,648 --> 00:55:39,208
...l'm in love with Don.

776
00:55:40,919 --> 00:55:42,716
Are you sure?

777
00:55:46,425 --> 00:55:48,188
And it's...

778
00:55:48,460 --> 00:55:51,623
It's nothing like I thought
it was going to be.

779
00:55:54,199 --> 00:55:56,190
It never is.

780
00:55:58,036 --> 00:56:01,028
You know, l...

781
00:56:01,873 --> 00:56:04,273
I used to dream that...

782
00:56:04,443 --> 00:56:07,207
...when I'd fall in love with a man...

783
00:56:07,379 --> 00:56:09,438
...he'd send me flowers...

784
00:56:09,614 --> 00:56:13,914
...sweep me off my feet,
take me in his arms.

785
00:56:16,221 --> 00:56:18,985
It's nothing like that with Don.

786
00:56:19,491 --> 00:56:22,790
He doesn't even know I'm alive,
half the time.

787
00:56:23,495 --> 00:56:25,929
When he sweeps me off my feet...

788
00:56:26,098 --> 00:56:28,123
...it's during a dance number.

789
00:56:28,300 --> 00:56:30,268
When he sends me flowers...

790
00:56:30,435 --> 00:56:33,063
...it's because it's good for business.

791
00:56:33,872 --> 00:56:36,306
Oh, he's taken me in his arms...

792
00:56:36,475 --> 00:56:41,174
...but there've never been less
than 700 people watching.

793
00:56:42,914 --> 00:56:45,007
Oh, it's not his fault.

794
00:56:45,183 --> 00:56:47,014
It's mine.

795
00:56:48,653 --> 00:56:51,383
When they were passing out the wishes...

796
00:56:54,092 --> 00:56:56,390
...I wished for him.

797
00:56:58,663 --> 00:57:01,291
Our dinner should be ready soon.

798
00:57:01,933 --> 00:57:03,958
I'm not very hungry.

799
00:57:04,136 --> 00:57:05,660
Neither am I. Should we go?

800
00:57:05,837 --> 00:57:07,464
Yeah.

801
00:57:16,314 --> 00:57:17,872
We're not staying.

802
00:57:18,049 --> 00:57:20,176
- You're not?
- No.

803
00:57:20,352 --> 00:57:22,877
Your hat and coat, Mr. Harrow.

804
00:58:09,201 --> 00:58:13,968
<i>There's an old superstition</i>
<i>Way down South</i>

805
00:58:14,339 --> 00:58:20,369
<i>Everybody believes</i>
<i>That trouble won't stay</i>

806
00:58:20,845 --> 00:58:25,475
<i>If you shake it away</i>

807
00:58:26,952 --> 00:58:31,787
<i>When they hold a revival</i>
<i>Way down South</i>

808
00:58:32,190 --> 00:58:38,652
<i>Everybody with care</i>
<i>And trouble that day</i>

809
00:58:39,130 --> 00:58:45,228
<i>Tries to shake it away</i>

810
00:58:45,470 --> 00:58:50,407
<i>Shakin' the blues away</i>
<i>Unhappy news away</i>

811
00:58:50,675 --> 00:58:55,908
<i>If you are blue, it's easy to</i>
<i>Shake off your cares and troubles</i>

812
00:58:56,081 --> 00:59:01,109
<i>Tellin' the blues to go</i>
<i>They may refuse to go</i>

813
00:59:01,386 --> 00:59:05,618
<i>But as a rule, they'll go if you'll</i>
<i>Shake 'em away</i>

814
00:59:05,790 --> 00:59:09,157
<i>Do like the voodoos do</i>
<i>Listenin' to</i>

815
00:59:09,361 --> 00:59:10,919
<i>A voodoo melody</i>

816
00:59:11,096 --> 00:59:14,930
<i>They shake their bodies so</i>
<i>To and fro</i>

817
00:59:15,100 --> 00:59:17,398
<i>With every shake</i>
<i>A lucky break</i>

818
00:59:17,569 --> 00:59:22,529
<i>Provin' that there's a way</i>
<i>To chase your cares away</i>

819
00:59:22,841 --> 00:59:27,471
<i>If you would lose your weary blues</i>
<i>Shake 'em away</i>

820
00:59:27,646 --> 00:59:30,740
<i>Shake 'em away</i>

821
01:00:49,361 --> 01:00:51,921
<i>Shakin' the blues away</i>

822
01:00:52,097 --> 01:00:54,565
<i>Unhappy news away</i>

823
01:00:54,833 --> 01:00:57,700
<i>If you are blue, it's easy to</i>
<i>Shake off your</i>

824
01:00:57,869 --> 01:01:00,360
<i>Shake off your cares</i>
<i>And shake off your troubles</i>

825
01:01:00,538 --> 01:01:05,635
<i>Show them that there's a way</i>
<i>To chase your cares away</i>

826
01:01:05,877 --> 01:01:10,371
<i>If you would lose your weary blues</i>
<i>Shake 'em away</i>

827
01:01:10,949 --> 01:01:13,782
<i>Shake 'em away</i>

828
01:01:13,952 --> 01:01:16,682
<i>Away</i>

829
01:01:21,526 --> 01:01:23,858
<i>Away</i>

830
01:01:43,915 --> 01:01:45,143
Hello?

831
01:01:45,316 --> 01:01:48,308
Hannah. Now, don't tell me
you're gonna break our date.

832
01:01:48,486 --> 01:01:51,182
Johnny, have you heard from Don?

833
01:01:51,356 --> 01:01:54,985
I haven't seen him since yesterday.
I've been calling everyplace.

834
01:01:55,193 --> 01:01:57,787
No. I wouldn't worry.
Nothing could've happened.

835
01:01:57,962 --> 01:02:00,988
You don't know how depressed he's been
the past few weeks.

836
01:02:01,166 --> 01:02:04,727
Then today, with the papers saying
what a big hit the <i>Follies</i> is.

837
01:02:04,903 --> 01:02:06,894
You know, he turned it down, and...

838
01:02:07,071 --> 01:02:08,299
I don't know.

839
01:02:08,473 --> 01:02:10,441
I'm so worried about him.

840
01:02:10,975 --> 01:02:12,340
Oh, wait a minute, Johnny.

841
01:02:12,510 --> 01:02:15,308
Will you hold the line?
There's somebody at the door.

842
01:02:18,049 --> 01:02:20,574
- Hello, baby!
- Don!

843
01:02:21,486 --> 01:02:24,751
- Where've you been? You read the reviews?
- Sure. Very good.

844
01:02:24,923 --> 01:02:27,187
- But wait till you read ours, baby.
- Ours?!

845
01:02:27,358 --> 01:02:29,758
- Dillingham wants us for a show.
- Dillingham?!

846
01:02:29,928 --> 01:02:33,056
Yeah! He called me this morning.
I've been with him all day.

847
01:02:33,231 --> 01:02:35,995
- He wants to build a show around us.
- Oh, Don!

848
01:02:36,167 --> 01:02:39,762
- Where's a calendar? A calendar!
- A calendar? A calendar! Here! Here!

849
01:02:39,938 --> 01:02:42,168
- Here's one.
- Yeah. Move over.

850
01:02:42,340 --> 01:02:44,365
Now, everything's all set.

851
01:02:44,542 --> 01:02:47,238
We start a week from Monday.
Four weeks' rehearsal.

852
01:02:47,412 --> 01:02:51,178
Four on the road, Philadelphia, Boston.
Opening in New York April 6th.

853
01:02:51,349 --> 01:02:53,408
Oh, Don, look!

854
01:02:53,585 --> 01:02:54,984
April 7th. What about it?

855
01:02:55,153 --> 01:02:58,520
Easter. We'll be here
for the Easter Parade.

856
01:02:58,690 --> 01:03:01,625
- That's right. We have a date, haven't we?
- Yes.

857
01:03:01,793 --> 01:03:04,523
- Say, how about celebrating tonight?
- Wonderful.

858
01:03:04,696 --> 01:03:06,664
- Go out and do the town.
- I'd love it!

859
01:03:06,831 --> 01:03:09,425
I better meet with the writers.
Pick me up, huh?

860
01:03:09,601 --> 01:03:11,364
- Right.
- Good.

861
01:03:12,837 --> 01:03:14,065
Eight o'clock.

862
01:03:14,239 --> 01:03:15,866
- Sharp.
- Sharp.

863
01:03:16,975 --> 01:03:18,772
Bye.

864
01:03:27,685 --> 01:03:29,209
Johnny, are you still there?

865
01:03:29,387 --> 01:03:30,877
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

866
01:03:31,055 --> 01:03:33,455
Yes, I'm still here.

867
01:03:34,592 --> 01:03:35,581
Congratulations.

868
01:03:36,995 --> 01:03:39,395
Did you hear? Isn't it wonderful?

869
01:03:39,797 --> 01:03:41,492
Yes, it's great.

870
01:03:41,666 --> 01:03:44,726
I hope you don't mind
if I break our date for tonight.

871
01:03:46,838 --> 01:03:48,430
Oh, Johnny.

872
01:03:48,606 --> 01:03:52,167
<i>That's all right.</i>
<i>We'll celebrate tomorrow night.</i>

873
01:03:54,679 --> 01:03:56,510
Thank you, Johnny.

874
01:03:56,681 --> 01:03:58,410
Bye.

875
01:04:03,855 --> 01:04:08,087
Operator. Plaza 3-1549.

876
01:04:09,460 --> 01:04:11,052
Hello, Nadine?

877
01:04:11,229 --> 01:04:14,756
Nadine, I'll be able to make it
for dinner tonight after all.

878
01:04:14,933 --> 01:04:16,798
Right.

879
01:04:35,820 --> 01:04:37,720
- Hello.
- I hope I'm not late.

880
01:04:37,889 --> 01:04:41,518
- You're right on time.
- Aren't we going out?

881
01:04:41,693 --> 01:04:44,389
I thought if you didn't mind,
we'd have dinner here.

882
01:04:44,562 --> 01:04:47,030
- I'd love it.
- Good.

883
01:04:47,198 --> 01:04:48,597
Champagne?

884
01:04:48,766 --> 01:04:50,563
Yeah.

885
01:04:51,603 --> 01:04:55,334
There won't be anybody to disturb us,
just the two of us.

886
01:04:59,877 --> 01:05:02,903
I thought we'd go over some new
ideas I have for the show.

887
01:05:03,081 --> 01:05:05,777
- There's one in particular I know...
- What?!

888
01:05:06,484 --> 01:05:08,714
What's the matter? What have I done?

889
01:05:09,087 --> 01:05:11,487
Nothing, that's what you've done.
Nothing.

890
01:05:11,656 --> 01:05:14,181
I thought we had a date tonight,
not a rehearsal.

891
01:05:14,359 --> 01:05:17,055
I should know better than to expect
you to be human.

892
01:05:17,228 --> 01:05:19,389
- You're just a pair of dance shoes.
- What?

893
01:05:19,564 --> 01:05:21,191
I'm tired of being a prop here!

894
01:05:21,366 --> 01:05:23,493
- I don't even feel like a girl!
- Listen...

895
01:05:23,668 --> 01:05:26,728
- You're just a pair of dancing shoes!
- You said that.

896
01:05:26,904 --> 01:05:28,132
I don't care!

897
01:05:28,306 --> 01:05:30,968
Besides, I bought a new dress!

898
01:05:31,476 --> 01:05:33,569
- It's pretty.
- You haven't even looked.

899
01:05:33,745 --> 01:05:35,713
- That's not true.
- Oh, isn't it?

900
01:05:35,880 --> 01:05:38,906
All right, then tell me:
What color are my eyes?

901
01:05:39,083 --> 01:05:43,713
You won't be able to answer that because
you have never paid enough attention to it.

902
01:05:48,459 --> 01:05:50,222
They're brown.

903
01:05:51,896 --> 01:05:53,591
That's right.

904
01:05:53,831 --> 01:05:56,459
- I'll get my hat and coat...
- Oh, no, please.

905
01:05:56,634 --> 01:05:58,067
Can't we stay here?

906
01:05:58,236 --> 01:06:00,204
- But you said...
- I know, but...

907
01:06:00,371 --> 01:06:02,271
...that was before.

908
01:06:02,440 --> 01:06:04,772
I don't mind now.

909
01:06:05,209 --> 01:06:07,040
All right.

910
01:06:12,617 --> 01:06:15,142
Fire is so pretty.

911
01:06:20,825 --> 01:06:23,350
"It Only Happens When I Dance With You."

912
01:06:23,528 --> 01:06:26,326
That's one of the old songs.

913
01:06:26,931 --> 01:06:28,489
She's very beautiful.

914
01:06:28,666 --> 01:06:32,158
Yes, but she doesn't mean anything
to me anymore.

915
01:06:32,804 --> 01:06:35,830
I told her I could teach any girl
to dance as well as she.

916
01:06:36,007 --> 01:06:37,474
And you have.

917
01:06:37,642 --> 01:06:40,338
No. We have.

918
01:06:40,912 --> 01:06:42,470
The idea was just this.

919
01:06:42,647 --> 01:06:47,949
I started out to prove something, and now
it isn't important anymore. That's all.

920
01:06:53,658 --> 01:07:00,962
<i>It only happens</i>
<i>When I dance with you</i>

921
01:07:02,500 --> 01:07:10,635
<i>That trip to heaven</i>
<i>Till the dance is through</i>

922
01:07:12,477 --> 01:07:20,213
<i>With no one else</i>
<i>Do the heavens seem quite so near</i>

923
01:07:20,818 --> 01:07:25,653
<i>Why does it happen, dear</i>

924
01:07:26,357 --> 01:07:31,260
<i>Only with you?</i>

925
01:07:34,065 --> 01:07:42,165
<i>Two cheeks together</i>
<i>Can be so divine</i>

926
01:07:42,974 --> 01:07:46,603
<i>But only when those cheeks</i>

927
01:07:46,778 --> 01:07:51,681
<i>Are yours and mine</i>

928
01:07:52,350 --> 01:07:56,844
<i>I've danced with dozens of others</i>

929
01:07:57,021 --> 01:08:04,325
<i>The whole night through</i>

930
01:08:05,196 --> 01:08:09,098
<i>But the thrill that comes with spring</i>

931
01:08:09,367 --> 01:08:15,499
<i>When anything could happen</i>

932
01:08:16,774 --> 01:08:22,337
<i>That only happens</i>

933
01:08:22,847 --> 01:08:28,752
<i>With you</i>

934
01:08:38,896 --> 01:08:41,660
Why didn't you tell me
I was in love with you?

935
01:08:55,513 --> 01:08:57,276
Come in.

936
01:08:57,648 --> 01:09:00,048
- Hi.
- Hi, how are you? Thanks for the flowers.

937
01:09:00,218 --> 01:09:01,742
- Nervous?
- No. Don't do that!

938
01:09:01,919 --> 01:09:04,251
Don't put your hat on the bed.
It's bad luck.

939
01:09:04,422 --> 01:09:06,151
